name: ToyCon UK Custom Little Ox - 'Lotus Ox' by Mr Lister
description:
Mr Lister custom of the Little Ox resin toy by alto x Creo Design

Edition of 1, especially created for ToyCon UK.

Little Ox is a hand cast and finished resin toy.

Little Ox stands approx. 3" high and 3" long.

The resin used in the production of the toy is a mix created especially for Creo Design and has its own unique weight and feel.

www.studioalto.co.uk
www.cdtoys.co.uk


Postage is via Special Delivery (UK) and 'Signed For' international shipping.

Please note : Little Ox is not suitable for children. It is a collectable, recommended for those aged 15+

name: The Complete Unfold
description:
Complete set of all 10 of the 'Unfold' series of prints - colour A3 (420mm x 297mm) Giclee digital prints, on heavyweight Permajet smooth 240gsm stock.

Comprises:

'Unmasked'
'SPLAT-AT'
'X-Tinguished'
'R2-DEID2'
'TIE-Died'
'Ink Bleed'
'Malformer I - Optimush'
'Malformer II - Bumbledbee'
'Power Down!'
'Warped'

Each print is an Edition of 50 and hand numbered.

The Unfold prints will ship rolled, in cardboard tubes, unless otherwise requested, via Special Delivery in UK and Signed For international shipping, elsewhere.

name: In Flux - 'Plutonium - Available At Every Drugstore' Edition - A2 Screenprint
description:
Limited edition screenprint, produced for the Back To The Future-themed 'Just In Time' show, 9th June 2012, Sho Gallery, Cardiff.

Edition of 10 single colour prints, with Glow-In-The-Dark coat overprint, creating a faint radioactive* emission. Individually numbered.

A2 format (594mm wide x 420mm high) on 270gsm mohawk acid free archival stock.


For all enquiries, please e-mail: info@studioalto.co.uk

www.studioalto.co.uk

twitter: @c_i_dobson


Print will ship rolled, in sturdy cardboard tube, via Special Delivery (UK), or International 'Signed For' shipping. unless otherwise requested.


Please note, posting of orders has now ceased for the Christmas period and will resume in the New Year (3rd Jan 2013). 

*not actually radioactive
